cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO. 

This paper deals with a computer vision problem of semantic segmentation in videos, specifically for joint labeling of actor and action categories. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes an end-to-end region-based approach that relies on instance segmentation masks, which involves deep learning techniques and could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of a two-stream network to capture both appearance and motion information, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper's focus on video segmentation could also fall under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics).
